HEADER Permissable skills and levels

  The selection of skills available in a guild naturally depends on 
  the type and the style of the guild. The style of the guild has to 
  be clearly defined and must be limited to one profession. So for 
  example a fighter-cleric guild will not be accepted. 

  However, one could for example create a guild which is an 
  occupational fighter guild and a layman cleric guild, occupying two 
  guild slots instead of one, where it is impossible to join only one 
  branch.

PRIMARY AND SECONDARY SKILL TYPES
  The type of skills a guild can train without skill cap penalty as 
  an alien skill are referred to here as as 'primary' skills, and 
  is determined by guild class.

